<meta name="assert" content="Auto hypenation and unicode-bidi 'plaintext' should not affect, hence the trailing ideographic spaces must hang; however, the rest of the sequence is wrapped due to the forced break.">
<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/fonts/ahem.css">
<style>
div {
    font: 2147483649px/0 Ahem;
    width: 1ch;
}
span {
    background: green;
    color: transparent;

    unicode-bidi: plaintext;
    hyphens: auto;
}
.ref {
  position: absolute;
  color: red;
  z-index: -1;
}
</style>

<p>Test passes if there is a <strong>filled green square</strong> and <strong><strong>no red</strong></strong>.</p>
<div class="ref">XX<br>XX</div>
<div><span>X&#x30px/0 Ahem;
    width: 98ch;
}
span {
    background: green square</strong> and <strong>no red</strong>.</p>
<div class="ref">XX<br>XX</div>
<div><span>X&#x2999;<br>XX</span></div>
